HEADWORD: Argosy
<hw>Ar"go*sy</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Argosies</plw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[Earlier
<ets>ragusy</ets>, fr. <ets>ragusa</ets> meaning orig. a vessel of
Ragusa.]</ety> <def>A large ship, esp. a merchant vessel of the largest
size.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Where your <qex>argosies</qex> with portly sail . . . ⟦br⟧
Do overpeer the petty traffickers.</q> <rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Argot</ent>⟦br⟧
